			//		and a method named `_setFooAttr()`, calling
			//		`myWidget.set("foo", "Howdy!")` would be equivalent to calling
			//		`widget._setFooAttr("Howdy!")` and `myWidget.set("bar", 3)`
			//		would be equivalent to the statement `widget.bar = 3;`
